/*
    WHAT THIS APP IS ATTEMPTING TO DO:
    This is a "Supervisor Hub" Task Assignment Manager built as a React-based PCF 
    (PowerApps Component Framework) control or Custom Page. It allows Supervisors 
    to visually manage shift workers by dragging and dropping "un-utilized" employees 
    into specific production "Areas" and "Equipment" overseen by "Leads". 

    TABLE ARCHITECTURE & SOURCE OF TRUTH:
    1. craa5_taskassignment (Primary Source of Truth): Used exclusively to load 
       presets, reconstruct the board state, and read current shift assignments.
    2. craa5__aa_eeutilization (Backup Log): STRICTLY WRITE-ONLY. We write to this 
       table for historical backup and reporting purposes, but NEVER read from it.
    3. craa5__aa_employee: Holds the roster and the `craa5_Utilized` boolean toggle.
    4. craa5_aa_mss_area: Master list of production areas.
    5. craa5_aa_assets: Master list of equipment/assets tied to specific areas.

    CRITICAL HISTORICAL LEARNINGS (DO NOT DEVIATE FROM THESE IN FUTURE EDITS):
    - [LEARNING 1: EXACT ODATA CASING]: Dataverse Web API strictly accepts LOGICAL NAMES for payloads, 
      which are 100% lowercase. FIX: When writing records, ALL keys MUST be lowercase.
    - [LEARNING 2: PCF VIEW DATA TRUNCATION]: Props passed natively from PowerApps truncate un-viewed columns.
      FIX: We completely bypass PCF inputs and use `fetchAllActiveRecords()` to query Dataverse directly.
    - [LEARNING 3: DATAVERSE PAGINATION BUGS]: Standard API calls cap at 50 records. 
      FIX: All fetches use a helper that sends `<fetch top='5000'>` XML to grab the entire table securely.
    - [LEARNING 8: DURATION TRACKING]: The app tracks exact duration an employee spends in a bucket. 
      This maps to `craa5__duration_assigned`.
    - [LEARNING 9: EMAIL PAYLOAD MAPPINGS & VALIDATION]: Emails must map to `craa5_email`, `craa5_leademail`, 
      and `craa5_supervisoremail`. Missing emails trigger a visual ✖ indicator.
    - [LEARNING 14: EQUIPMENT TREE & SUB-BUCKETS]: A new step queries equipment to render nested dropzones, 
      routing assignment data to the `craa5_equip` and `craa5_equipment` payload fields.
    - [LEARNING 16: GLOBAL EMPLOYEE LOOKUP]: Restricting the employee pool to only active shift members 
      caused off-shift employees (restored from presets) to lose their associated email payload during submission. 
      FIX: Introduced a global `allEmployees` state hash map to guarantee total profile restoration.
    - [LEARNING 18: FLUENT UI INPUT FALLBACKS]: PowerApps environments often proxy native DOM events instead 
      of synthetic `(e, data)` objects. If `data?.value` is called blindly, inputs lock up and checkboxes freeze.
      FIX: All `<Input>` and `<Checkbox>` components strictly use inline fallbacks: `d?.value ?? e.target?.value ?? ""`
    - [LEARNING 19: AUTOMATIC SHIFT IMPERSONATION]: Instead of trying to match the user's specific email 
      to an off-shift supervisor profile, the app calculates the active shift and forces impersonation of 
      that supervisor, instantly granting `adminMode` for managers.
    - [LEARNING 20: UNIVERSAL ACCESS / NO READ-ONLY]: All off-shift, impersonation, and read-only UI 
      locks (`disabled={isReadOnly}`) have been entirely stripped from the app. All users have full write access.
    - [LEARNING 21: INFINITE RENDER LOOP ASSASSINATION]: Background timers attempting to write to `localStorage` 
      in sandboxed iframes throw silent DOM exceptions, triggering infinite `useEffect` loops that freeze the 
      main thread (locking inputs). PCF `updateView` also re-injects prop array references continuously.
      FIX: `localStorage` is eradicated. Dependencies rely strictly on `.length` primitive hashes to prevent 
      reference cascading and infinite re-renders.
    - [LEARNING 23: DYNAMIC AREA CATEGORIZATION]: Area Selection was upgraded to a 3-column drag-and-drop board 
      ("Supporting", "Production", "Assigned") driven by the `craa5_production` Dataverse yes/no flag.
    - [LEARNING 24: CSS BOX-SIZING CLIPPING]: 100% height wrappers with padding will clip out the bottom of 
      scrollable lists if `boxSizing: 'border-box'` is not strictly enforced on the parent layout container.
    - [LEARNING 25: CONCISE HEADCOUNT EXPORT]: The clipboard formatting uses a `getAreaEmoji` helper to append 
      scannable icons. Headcount mode eliminates the bottom attendance block, instead consolidating PTO/Sick/Late 
      at the top of the export, and formatting areas to a highly condensed `({count}) {Area}` format.

    HOW TO RECREATE THIS APP FROM SCRATCH (PROMPT):
    "Create a React application using @fluentui/react-components designed for a Power Apps / PCF environment. 
    The app is a 'Supervisor Hub' for task management. It requires a step-by-step wizard.
    Data must be fetched and written using either a passed-in `dataApi` prop or a safely extracted `Xrm.WebApi`."
*/
